{"meals":[{"idMeal":"53173","strMeal":"Quick gazpacho","strMealAlternate":null,"strCategory":"Starter","strArea":"Spanish","strCountry":"Spain","strInstructions":"step 1\r\nIn a blender (or with a stick blender), whizz together the passata, red pepper, chilli, garlic, sherry vinegar and lime juice until smooth. Season to taste, then serve with ice cubes","strMealThumb":"https:\/\/www.themealdb.com\/images\/media\/meals\/h5qmn31763304965.jpg","strTags":null,"strYoutube":"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=sJzHIxlDTHc","strIngredient1":"Passata","strIngredient2":"Red Pepper","strIngredient3":"Red Chilli","strIngredient4":"Garlic","strIngredient5":"Sherry vinegar","strIngredient6":"Lime","strIngredient7":"","strIngredient8":"","strIngredient9":"","strIngredient10":"","strIngredient11":"","strIngredient12":"","strIngredient13":"","strIngredient14":"","strIngredient15":"","strIngredient16":"","strIngredient17":"","strIngredient18":"","strIngredient19":"","strIngredient20":"","strMeasure1":"250g","strMeasure2":"1 chopped","strMeasure3":"1 chopped","strMeasure4":"1 clove peeled crushed","strMeasure5":"1 teaspoon","strMeasure6":"Juice of 1\/2","strMeasure7":" ","strMeasure8":" ","strMeasure9":" ","strMeasure10":" ","strMeasure11":" ","strMeasure12":" ","strMeasure13":" ","strMeasure14":" ","strMeasure15":" ","strMeasure16":" ","strMeasure17":" ","strMeasure18":" ","strMeasure19":" ","strMeasure20":" ","strSource":"https:\/\/www.bbcgoodfood.com\/recipes\/quick-gazpacho","strImageSource":null,"strCreativeCommonsConfirmed":null,"dateModified":"2025-11-16 14:52:54"},{"idMeal":"53108","strMeal":"Quick salt & pepper squid","strMealAlternate":null,"strCategory":"Seafood","strArea":"Australian","strCountry":"Australia","strInstructions":"step 1\r\nAsk the fishmonger to clean the squid; little ones often come ready-cleaned. Using kitchen scissors, cut open the body and open out. Wash well, then pat dry. If you have a large squid, cut the body into four portions, roughly square. Small squid can just be opened up.\r\n\r\nstep 2\r\nUsing the tip of a very sharp knife, score the top in a neat criss-cross. Brush with oil and set aside while you heat the barbecue or griddle until ready to cook.\r\n\r\nstep 3\r\nMix together 2 tsp sea salt, Chinese five-spice and 1 tsp freshly ground black pepper. Sprinkle on both sides of the squid just before cooking, according to taste. You may not need it all. Heat the griddle pan to hot and cook about 1 min each side, until it starts to curl. Remove with tongs to a serving plate and drizzle with a little sesame oil. To serve, garnish with coriander leaves and serve with small bowls of sweet chilli sauce to dip into.","strMealThumb":"https:\/\/www.themealdb.com\/images\/media\/meals\/cp74zo1762341241.jpg","strTags":null,"strYoutube":"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=CxHTj_6sU_A","strIngredient1":"Squid","strIngredient2":"Oil","strIngredient3":"Chinese five spice powder","strIngredient4":"Sesame Seed Oil","strIngredient5":"Coriander","strIngredient6":"sweet chilli sauce","strIngredient7":"","strIngredient8":"","strIngredient9":"","strIngredient10":"","strIngredient11":"","strIngredient12":"","strIngredient13":"","strIngredient14":"","strIngredient15":"","strIngredient16":"","strIngredient17":"","strIngredient18":"","strIngredient19":"","strIngredient20":"","strMeasure1":"400g","strMeasure2":"3  tablespoons","strMeasure3":"1\/2 teaspoon","strMeasure4":"Dash","strMeasure5":"Sprigs of fresh","strMeasure6":"Drizzle","strMeasure7":" ","strMeasure8":" ","strMeasure9":" ","strMeasure10":" ","strMeasure11":" ","strMeasure12":" ","strMeasure13":" ","strMeasure14":" ","strMeasure15":" ","strMeasure16":" ","strMeasure17":" ","strMeasure18":" ","strMeasure19":" ","strMeasure20":" ","strSource":"https:\/\/www.bbcgoodfood.com\/recipes\/salt-pepper-squid-0","strImageSource":null,"strCreativeCommonsConfirmed":null,"dateModified":"2025-11-05 02:58:23"}]}